originalText.text:
Do NOT go there. I just reported them to my insurance and BBB. Horrible office, the girls at the reception desk are clueless and very rude. On numerous occasions I called this office to schedule appointments for different reasons, one time it was for my carpal tunnel and the girl at the front said they don’t do it and that I should come in at 6am every morning in hopes of seeing a doctor since they don’t take appointments, I told her she doesn’t know what she is talking about because my primary doctor THAT WORKS THERE specifically told me about the hand doctor in their facility, after going back and forth with her (she also spoke very bad English) another girl finally scheduled me. The front desk people are incredibly rude, I can’t stress that enough, I also don’t understand who trains them since they don’t even know which doctors come when. I also did a couple of tests for my heart a couple of months ago and I have yet to see any results because the girls at the front desk wouldn’t schedule me and keep telling me to come in at 6am every day and wait because they are BUSY. This is not a free clinic, where no one takes insurance and makes people wait!!!! Obviously I’m changing my primary doctor. This office keeps taking on more and more patients taking their insurance money while I’m being yelled at by a clueless front desk girl and am not being able to schedule an appointment in months!
Horrible, rude, unprofessional!!!

He's a great human being that listen to you with attention and that'll try his best to help you out with your health situation.
